Atticus in the
second book turned out to be a
conventional

50:54.151 --> 51:00.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
racist like the other people on
the town council.
So I think it was a mistake for
her reputation.

51:00.190 --> 51:04.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the singular book that she
will be remembered
for is the "Mockingbird."

51:04.361 --> 51:06.196 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

51:06.297 --> 51:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes. I was going
to say, so,
briefly, the legacy really, you
just think,

51:09.133 --> 51:13.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should be defined by one this
book, but what
a book it was.

51:13.537 --> 51:16.407 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ALLAN GURGANUS: What a book it
was.

51:16.507 --> 51:24.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to think that it came out in
1960, just
before the huge riots and the
German shepherds

51:24.782 --> 51:30.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the fire hoses in the South,
I think it
taught white America how to
think about race.

51:30.220 --> 51:35.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we needed an innocent child
to lead us
into that difficult and complex
subject.

51:35.259 --> 51:43.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it made the prophecy of what
was coming
palatable and easy to understand
and digest.

51:43.968 --> 51:49.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it served an extraordinary
function, and
it's to be remembered and
treasured, I think.

51:49.206 --> 51:56.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Allan Gurganus on
the life
and work of Harper Lee, thank
you so much.

